Human rights activist Maina Kiai was detained at JKIA after immigration officials asked him for travel clearance.He was due to catch a flight at 7.50am but the immigration people refused to stamp his passport.The immigration supervisor at the airport Nancy Nganga didn't say why Kiai needs clearance yet he isn't a government official.Recently, KHRC ran into trouble with state after the coordination board ordered its accounts frozen.Kiai is a board member of the charitable organisation.They obtained orders from a court stopping NGO coordination board boss Fazul Mahamed from executing the freeze order.Later, immigration allowed him to leave.